	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f110137932837640>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=17179&mid=110137932837640>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=17179&mid=110137932837640>Wrong</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=17179&mid=110137932837640#post><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11"></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Nov 25th 5:42 AM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=/db/poster.html?user=167289><span id= >Mahrk</span></a><br><span id=notbold>9 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I've been using one of these in secondary for a few levels now.&nbsp;&nbsp;This weapon does proc quite frequently for me with my dex at 255. The loss of agi isn't even noticeable, and agi is one of my lowest stats.  What is noticeable is that while the proc buff is up, you are immune to harm touch/lifetap effects.  I first noticed this while farming smithing materials from the shadows in Twilight Sea.  And since it completely blocked the lifetaps, the amount of damage those lifetaps would have done was not counted against 200 absorbed damage limit of the proc.  Despite the lifetaps, the buff stayed up until 200 points of physical damage was absorbed or until 5 minutes had passed, whichever came first. </p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Mahrk Lonefeather<br>Ranger-Outrider of the 59th Season<br>Solusek Ro<br></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>0 Replies</td></tr>
	     </form></table>
