<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f109733622371925>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=17179&mid=109733622371925>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=17179&mid=109733622371925>It sucks more than you think. Here's why.</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=17179&mid=109733622371925#post><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11"></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sat, Oct 9th 11:37 AM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=/db/poster.html?user=390555><span id= >Jemnisimi</span></a><br><span id=notbold>11 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Here's my 2cp on it.<br><br>Let's face it. The stats on this weapon could use some work, especially with the stuff coming out these days but it's aside from the point. The damage/delay ratio's fine, but the killer is the proc. It has a proc mod which makes it proc more often than average, so I've heard. Which sounds even more appealing to the masses. Until you take into account that this rune also takes away 20 agility when it's cast, meaning, obviously, you get hit more often when casting it. Not by too much, but when you judge the rate, you may as well negate that 20 agi permenantly. The damage you take starts adding up after that much loss, especially if you're not a twink.<br><br>When you hit level 55, most mobs are gonna be hitting you for the upwards of 400hp or more. If your character is vastly superior in level to the mob then this is fine because you'll naturally get hit less. <br><br>But in most situations, this effect just assures that something is going to hit you. &quot;Here I have protection now, come smack me for twice what I can absorb.&quot;. Right, well, point is, you can only start using this thing after the effect on it is useless virtually. It's a nice aggro weapon, and I think saying that the effect on it is a curse is overexaggerating it, but the reward is minimal at best in comparison to many other choices.<br><br>Now on the other hand, $$$ farming weapon especially if you're not adept at healing yourself. But, this is a tank weapon really, unless you're some other class that just really likes getting hit and thinks your bind spot's intellectually stimulating.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
